cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the use of user-generated content (Wikipedia) for news reporting, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The development of a news-reader also involves aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SI). Additionally, the analysis of the timing of news reporting on Wikipedia compared to traditional news sources could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or systems and control (cs.SD).
